  "description": "This [genealogy](../../../../../../humanities/domains/philosophy/disciplines/critical-theory/schools/foucault/terms/genealogy.md) treats card games as related rule systems built from recurring parts: deck construction, information distribution, turn sequencing, comparative resolution, and scoring loops. Names and themes change, but many designs inherit and recombine the same mechanical primitives.",
